author: will.
content: look, i get it, school can feel like a waste of time sometimes, especially when there are a million other things you’d rather be doing. but at the end of the day, focusing on school is about setting yourself up for options. it’s not just about grades or following rules; it’s about making sure you’re not stuck later wishing you had taken it more seriously. when you actually put effort into school, you’re giving yourself more choices in life. you don’t have to know exactly what you want to do yet, but if you slack off now, you might regret it when opportunities come up and you’re not ready for them. it’s not about being a straight-a student or acting like school is your whole life it’s about making sure you’re not closing doors before you even realize you might want to walk through them. at the end of the day, education is one of the few things that no one can take away from you. the effort you put in now pays off later, even if it doesn’t seem like it in the moment. so yeah, it might not always be fun, but if you handle business now, you’ll thank yourself later.
